ence\u002F3.abac-expression-language","i-lucide-file-code",{"title":182,"path":183,"stem":184,"icon":185},"CRI Format","\u002Freference\u002Fcri-format","3.reference\u002F4.cri-format","i-lucide-link",{"title":187,"path":188,"stem":189,"icon":190},"SDK Packages","\u002Freference\u002Fsdk-packages","3.reference\u002F5.sdk-packages","i-lucide-package",{"id":192,"title":25,"body":193,"description":334,"extension":335,"links":336,"meta":337,"navigation":338,"path":65,"seo":339,"stem":66,"__hash__":340},"docs\u002F1.apps\u002F5.persistence\u002F1.overview.md",{"type":194,"value":195,"toc":327},"minimark",[196,200,205,251,255,258,286,290,293],[197,198,199],"p",{},"Kinotic provides a declarative persistence layer. You define entities with TypeScript decorators, and Kinotic generates fully typed CRUD services automatically, including full-text search, pagination, and more.",[201,202,204],"h2",{"id":203},"key-features","Key Features",[206,207,208,216,227,233,239,245],"ul",{},[209,210,211,215],"li",{},[212,213,214],"strong",{},"Automatic CRUD generation"," - Define an entity class and get a complete service with create, read, update, delete, search, and count operations",[209,217,218,221,222,226],{},[212,219,220],{},"Full-text search"," - Mark fields with ",[223,224,225],"code",{},"@Text"," to enable full-text search out of the box",[209,228,229,232],{},[212,230,231],{},"Schema evolution"," - Use versioned migration scripts to evolve your data schema safely over time",[209,234,235,238],{},[212,236,237],{},"Multi-tenancy"," - Built-in tenant isolation at the data layer with shared index support",[209,240,241,244],{},[212,242,243],{},"Named queries"," - Define custom query methods with a SQL-like syntax",[209,246,247,250],{},[212,248,249],{},"Attribute-based access control (ABAC)"," - Fine-grained data access policies applied at the persistence layer",[201,252,254],{"id":253},"workflow","Workflow",[197,256,257],{},"The typical workflow for working with Kinotic persistence is:",[259,260,261,270,280],"ol",{},[209,262,263,266,267],{},[212,264,265],{},"Define your entity"," - Create a TypeScript class with decorators from ",[223,268,269],{},"@kinotic-ai\u002Fpersistence",[209,271,272,275,276,279],{},[212,273,274],{},"Sync to server"," - Run ",[223,277,278],{},"kinotic sync"," to push your entity definitions to the Kinotic server and generate typed service classes",[209,281,282,285],{},[212,283,284],{},"Use in your app"," - Import and use the generated services to perform data operations",[201,287,289],{"id":288},"packages","Packages",[197,291,292],{},"Two packages work together to provide the persistence layer:",[206,294,295,315],{},[209,296,297,301,302,305,306,305,309,305,312,314],{},[212,298,299],{},[223,300,269],{}," - Provides entity decorators (",[223,303,304],{},"@Entity",", ",[223,307,308],{},"@AutoGeneratedId",[223,310,311],{},"@NotNull",[223,313,225],{},", etc.), entity service interfaces, and the persistence plugin",[209,316,317,322,323,326],{},[212,318,319],{},[223,320,321],{},"@kinotic-ai\u002Fcore"," - Provides the connection layer (",[223,324,325],{},"Kinotic.connect()","), pagination types, and core utilities shared across all Kinotic packages",{"title":328,"searchDepth":329,"depth":329,"links":330},"",2,[331,332,333],{"id":203,"depth":329,"text":204},{"id":253,"depth":329,"text":254},{"id":288,"depth":329,"text":289},"Kinotic's persistence layer provides declarative data management with automatic CRUD service generation from TypeScript entity definitions.","md",null,{},true,{"title":25,"description":334},"o2EFnpwTruJ_z7UzifMRaC_aOKFlVk2PgPruhC06Z68",[342,344],{"title":55,"path":56,"stem":57,"description":343,"children":-1},"Real-time data streaming between services and clients.",{"title":68,"path":69,"stem":70,"description":345,"children":-1},"How to define entities using TypeScript decorators for Kinotic's persistence layer.",1776745209624]